section.section:
Consent to adoption under this subtitle is not valid unless the consent:
is given after the prospective adoptee is born;
is given in a language that the party understands;
if given in a language other than English:
contains an express notice of:
except as to an adoption by a spouse of the prospective adoptee's parent or a relative of the prospective adoptee, states that the parent has been advised of the parent's rights to:
states whether the parent chose to have or not have counsel or counseling; and
is accompanied by an affidavit of counsel appointed under § 5-3B-06 of this subtitle stating that a parent who is a minor or has a disability gives consent knowingly and voluntarily.
